---
name: sdk-apps-check-parameter-limit
type: command
description: Validate that all Search, List, and Watch modules contain a proper Limit parameter with correct UX help message.
---

You must ask the user for the Make custom app name if it is not provided.

Target app: {{app_name}}

Use the Make API MCP server to locate the custom app with exact name: {{app_name}}.

Do NOT modify anything in the app.
This command is strictly read-only.

Steps:

1. Load all modules of the app.
2. Filter only modules of type:
   - Search
   - List
   - Watch

3. Use the Make API MCP server code and UX guidelines to check for each module:
   - Check if a parameter named exactly `limit` (case-insensitive) exists among mappable parameters.
   - Verify the parameter has correct settings and the help message follows UX guidelines for Limit parameters.

4. Collect only modules that fail any of the above checks.

Output requirements:

Result should be a list of modules with errors.